│  39 /// type is ever created.  Thus seeing if two types are equal is a      │
│ matter of                                                                   │
│  40 /// doing a trivial pointer comparison. To enforce that no two equal    │
│ instances                                                                   │
│  41 /// are created, Type instances can only be created via static factory  │
│ methods                                                                     │
│  42 /// in class Type and in derived classes.  Once allocated, Types are    │
│ never                                                                       │
│  43 /// free'd.                                                             │
│  44 ///                                                                     │
